{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SrdTMeCBVxpeRyCsfQRUZn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a final summary document of all my findings:\n\n## Summary of Source Code Changes and Documentation\n\nI have thoroughly reviewed the modified source code files and all relevant documentation. Here's a comprehensive analysis of the three-phase orchestration loop and related systems:\n\n### **Three-Phase Orchestration Loop Overview**\n\nThe codebase implements a new three-phase orchestration pattern for host workflows with the following structure:\n\n1. **List-Tasks Phase**: Discover available work by running the list-tasks workflow\n2. **Main Phase**: Execute the main workflow for each open task (up to MaxConcurrent concurrent tasks)\n3. **Finalize Phase**: Run cleanup/post-processing after main completes (on both success and failure)\n\n---\n\n### **Key Source Files Modified**\n\n#### **1. `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`** (Core Three-Phase Implementation)\n\n**Key Concepts:**\n- **LoopConfig**: Configuration for orchestration (ProjectDir, MaxConcurrent, StaggerDelay, DedupTimeout)\n- **ListTasksFunc**: `func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) ([]Task, error)` - discovers available tasks\n- **MainFunc**: `func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, taskID string) (*RunResult, error)` - executes main workflow for a task\n- **FinalizeFunc**: `func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, taskID string, mainResult *RunResult) (*RunResult, error)` - optional cleanup after main completes\n- **Loop struct**: Manages continuous orchestration with support for both legacy (single-function) and three-phase modes\n\n**Three-Phase Loop Implementation (`runPhased()` method - lines 155-241):**\n1. Maintains concurrent limit with slot-filling logic\n2. Calls `pickTaskFromPhase()` to discover available work (line 187)\n3. Launches goroutines for each task that execute both main and finalize (lines 192-215):\n   - Phase 2 (Main): Executes the main workflow with context.Background() (line 198)\n   - Phase 3 (Finalize): Runs finalize if configured, on both success and failure (lines 207-212)\n4. Implements deduplication to prevent reassignment of the same task within DedupTimeout window (lines 256-265)\n5. Backsoff on failure with idlePollInterval (30 seconds) and immediately retries on success\n\n**Task Filtering:**\n- `pickTaskFromPhase()` (lines 246-283) uses `task.IsOpen()` to filter only open tasks\n- Tasks in non-open status (closed, in-progress) are skipped\n\n**Legacy Support:**\n- `NewLoop()` for single-function mode (existing behavior)\n- `NewPhaseLoop()` for three-phase mode (new)\n- `runLegacy()` maintains backward compatibility\n\n---\n\n#### **2. `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`** (Task Structures)\n\n**Task Structure** (lines 22-28):\n```go\ntype Task struct {\n    ID          string            `json:\"id\"`\n    Status      string            `json:\"status\"`\n    Title       string            `json:\"title\"`\n    Description string            `json:\"description\"`\n    Metadata    map[string]string `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**TaskStatus Constants** (lines 15-19):\n- `TaskStatusOpen = \"open\"`\n- `TaskStatusClosed = \"closed\"`\n- `TaskStatusInProgress = \"in-progress\"`\n\n**IsOpen() Method** (lines 31-33): Returns true if status is \"open\" or empty (backward compatible)\n\n**Task Parsing:**\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner`: Runs shell command, parses JSON array output (lines 42-67)\n- `ParseTasksJSONL()` (lines 72-89): Parses JSONL format (one JSON object per line) for list-tasks output\n  - Each line represents one task\n  - Empty lines are skipped\n  - Returns error on invalid JSON\n\n**ReadListTasksOutput()** in loop.go (lines 440-473): Utility to read output directory from list-tasks run and parse JSONL\n\n---\n\n#### **3. `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`** (Step Execution)\n\n**Executor Structure** (lines 51-63):\n- `TaskID`: Optional task ID assigned by daemon loop (line 61)\n- `ExtraEnv`: Additional environment variables passed to all steps (line 62)\n- `HostRunID`: ID of parent host run (line 58)\n\n**Environment Variables Passed to Steps** (lines 95-122):\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`: Project directory (line 96)\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`: Output file path for the step (line 97)\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`: Daemon-assigned task ID (line 102)\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`: Previous step's output (line 112)\n- Additional output mappings from wires (lines 116-122)\n- ExtraEnv variables (e.g., finalize phase outcome vars) (lines 105-108)\n\n**Step Types Executed** (lines 78-87):\n- Script steps (run shell commands)\n- Workflow steps (dispatch container workflows)\n- Agent steps (run coding agents on host)\n\n---\n\n#### **4. `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`** (Workflow Execution)\n\n**RunResult Structure** (lines 29-34):\n```go\ntype RunResult struct {\n    RunID     string\n    State     domain.RunState\n    OutputDir string\n}\n```\n\n**Named Workflow Execution:**\n- `RunNamed()` (lines 50-53): Executes a named workflow from host.cloche\n- `runNamedWorkflow()` (lines 57-149): Core implementation\n  - Parses `dsl.ParseAllForHost()` to get multiple workflows from host.cloche (line 64)\n  - Looks up specific workflow by name (lines 69-72)\n  - Creates output directory at `.cloche/<orchRunID>/output` (lines 75-78)\n  - Persists host run as IsHost=true in store (lines 83-90)\n  - Creates Executor with TaskID and ExtraEnv propagation (lines 92-102)\n\n**Workflow-Level Agent Configuration** (lines 105-110):\n- `host.agent_command` and `host.agent_args` keys\n- Parsed and passed to executor for agent steps\n\n---\n\n#### **5. `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`** (Multiple Workflows)\n\n**ParseAllForHost()** (lines 45-67):\n- Parses host.cloche files containing multiple workflows\n- Returns `map[string]*domain.Workflow`\n- Validates no duplicate workflow names (lines 56-58)\n- Requires at least one workflow (lines 62-64)\n\n**Location Validation** (line 156):\n- Sets `domain.LocationHost` for host workflows\n- Enables location-based validation\n\n---\n\n#### **6. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** (Daemon Integration)\n\n**ClocheServer Fields** (lines 28-41):\n- `loops`: `map[string]*host.Loop` - orchestration loop per project (line 40)\n- `runIDs`: Track run_id -> container_id mapping\n\n**Server Initialization:**\n- `NewClocheServer()` initializes loops map (line 48)\n- `NewClocheServerWithCaptures()` adds capture and log store support (line 59)\n\n**Orchestration Loop Not Directly Shown** in excerpts, but the server manages lifecycle and dispatches workflows that feed into the loop\n\n---\n\n### **Documentation Files**\n\n#### **1. `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`** (Complete)\n\n**Workflow Locations**:\n- **Container workflows**: Run in Docker containers via cloche-agent (script or agent steps only)\n- **Host workflows**: Run on host machine as daemon process (script, agent, or workflow steps)\n\n**Step Types**:\n- **agent** (has `prompt`): Invokes coding agent\n- **script** (has `run`): Runs shell command\n- **workflow** (has `workflow_name`): Dispatches container workflow (host only)\n\n**Host Workflow Example** (lines 160-192):\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n    CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output[0].id,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY = output[0].description\n  ]\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n**Wire Output Mappings** (lines 101-133):\n- Extract values from step output and inject as environment variables\n- Support JSON path expressions: `output`, `output.key`, `output[N]`, `output.a.b.c`, etc.\n\n**Host Configuration Block** (lines 136-154):\n- `host {}` block for workflow-level agent defaults\n- Supports `agent_command` and `agent_args`\n- Step-level overrides take priority\n\n**Execution Model** (lines 199-212):\n- Container workflows: Agent walks graph inside container\n- Host workflows: Daemon walks graph on host; scripts run from main git worktree\n- Environment variables injected: `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, etc.\n\n---\n\n#### **2. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`** (System Architecture)\n\n**System Components**:\n- **cloche** (CLI): Short-lived client\n- **cloched** (Daemon): Long-running orchestrator\n- **cloche-agent** (In-Container): Autonomous agent\n\n**Execution Model**:\n- One container per workflow run\n- All steps execute in same container\n- Container lifecycle: pull/build image → copy project → start container → stream status → extract results → stop\n\n**Communication**:\n- Agent <-> Daemon: JSON-lines over stdout\n- CLI <-> Daemon: gRPC\n\n**Capture System**: Record step inputs/outputs/results for replay\n\n---\n\n#### **3. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`** (Host Workflow Design)\n\n**Problem Solved**: Extension point for custom orchestration strategies\n\n**Solution**: `host.cloche` file with special workflow location for host execution\n\n**New Step Type: `workflow`**:\n- `workflow_name` config key dispatches container workflow\n- `prompt_step` optional override for which step's output to read\n- Results: `success` (RunStateSucceeded), `fail` (RunStateFailed/RunStateCancelled)\n\n**Step Output Capture**:\n- Every host step writes output to: `.cloche/<orch-run-id>/output/<step_name>.out`\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` passed to next step\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` tells step where to write its output\n\n**Environment Variables Injected** (lines 92-105):\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`: Task being processed\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE`: Task summary\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_BODY`: Full task description\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`: Project directory path\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`: Where step writes output\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`: Previous step's output file\n\n**Default `host.cloche`** (lines 180-199):\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  prepare-prompt:fail -> abort\n  develop:success -> done\n  develop:fail -> done\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Test Coverage**\n\n#### **`/workspace/internal/host/loop_test.go`**\n\n**Legacy Mode Tests**:\n- `TestLoop_StartStop`: Basic start/stop\n- `TestLoop_RampsUpOnSuccess`: Immediate retry on success, backoff on failure\n- `TestLoop_TaskAssigner_PassesTaskID`: Task ID propagation\n- `TestLoop_TaskAssigner_DedupPreventsReassignment`: Deduplication window\n- `TestLoop_TaskAssigner_DedupExpires`: Dedup timeout expiration\n\n**Three-Phase Mode Tests** (NewPhaseLoop):\n- `TestPhaseLoop_BasicFlow`: list-tasks → main → finalize flow\n- `TestPhaseLoop_SkipsClosedTasks`: Only picks open tasks\n- `TestPhaseLoop_FinalizeRunsOnFailure`: Finalize receives failed state\n- `TestPhaseLoop_NoFinalize`: Optional finalize (nil is valid)\n- `TestPhaseLoop_DedupFiltersOpenTasks`: Dedup works across phases\n\n#### **`/workspace/internal/host/task_test.go`**\n\n**ScriptTaskAssigner Tests**:\n- JSON array parsing\n- Empty array handling\n- Command failures\n- Invalid JSON handling\n- Partial fields\n\n**JSONL Parsing Tests**:\n- Basic JSONL with multiple tasks\n- Metadata fields\n- Empty lines\n- Invalid JSON in middle of JSONL\n- Task status variations\n\n**Task.IsOpen() Tests**:\n- Status field values: \"open\" (true), \"\" (true for backward compat), \"closed\" (false), \"in-progress\" (false)\n\n#### **`/workspace/internal/host/executor_test.go`**\n\n**Output Mapping Tests**: Large test file testing:\n- Output mapping from wires\n- Step output file capture\n- Environment variable injection\n- Executor setup with tasks, projects, etc.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Architectural Patterns**\n\n1. **Three-Phase Separation of Concerns**:\n   - List-Tasks: Pure discovery (reads external state)\n   - Main: Work execution (full computation)\n   - Finalize: Cleanup/side effects (post-execution)\n\n2. **Deduplication Strategy**: \n   - Prevents rapid reassignment of same task\n   - Timeout-based window (default 5 minutes)\n   - Stored per-loop instance in memory\n\n3. **Concurrent Slot Management**:\n   - Up to MaxConcurrent (default 1) active runs\n   - Stagger delay between launches to avoid race conditions\n   - Immediate retry on success, idle backoff on failure\n\n4. **Environment Variable Propagation**:\n   - Task metadata (ID, title, body) injected into steps\n   - Previous output passed as `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`\n   - Wire output mappings extract/transform values\n   - ExtraEnv for finalize phase outcome variables\n\n5. **Output File Organization**:\n   - Per-step: `.cloche/<orch-run-id>/output/<step_name>.out`\n   - Findable by ReadListTasksOutput() for JSONL parsing\n\n6. **Backward Compatibility**:\n   - NewLoop() for legacy single-function mode\n   - NewPhaseLoop() for three-phase\n   - Both coexist; selection based on which functions are set\n\n---\n\n### **File Paths (Absolute)**\n\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`\n- `/workspace/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/workspace/README.md`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4342570441c8690c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68846\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 59181</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5ceff1a-0d2b-4db0-a018-cacf9a2b2a3f","uuid":"f74d802d-d4d8-44cc-95f8-cb54ac6374e9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand two things:\n\n1. The current source code changes related to a three-phase orchestration loop (list-tasks, main, finalize). Look at these modified files:\n   - internal/host/executor.go\n   - internal/host/executor_test.go\n   - internal/host/loop.go\n   - internal/host/loop_test.go\n   - internal/host/runner.go\n   - internal/host/task.go\n   - internal/host/task_test.go\n   - internal/dsl/parser.go\n   - internal/dsl/parser_test.go\n   - internal/adapters/grpc/server.go\n\nFor each file, read the full contents and note key concepts: phases (list-tasks, main, finalize), task structures (JSONL parsing, task fields like id/status/title/description), environment variables passed to workflows, how the daemon orchestrates the three phases.\n\n2. All documentation files that might reference the orchestration loop, host workflows, or workflow phases. Check:\n   - docs/workflows.md\n   - docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md\n   - Any other .md files under docs/\n   - CLAUDE.md (already known)\n   - README.md if it exists\n\nRead all documentation files fully so we can compare against the source code.\n\nBe very thorough - read every file completely.","agentId":"a4342570441c8690c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a final summary document of all my findings:\n\n## Summary of Source Code Changes and Documentation\n\nI have thoroughly reviewed the modified source code files and all relevant documentation. Here's a comprehensive analysis of the three-phase orchestration loop and related systems:\n\n### **Three-Phase Orchestration Loop Overview**\n\nThe codebase implements a new three-phase orchestration pattern for host workflows with the following structure:\n\n1. **List-Tasks Phase**: Discover available work by running the list-tasks workflow\n2. **Main Phase**: Execute the main workflow for each open task (up to MaxConcurrent concurrent tasks)\n3. **Finalize Phase**: Run cleanup/post-processing after main completes (on both success and failure)\n\n---\n\n### **Key Source Files Modified**\n\n#### **1. `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`** (Core Three-Phase Implementation)\n\n**Key Concepts:**\n- **LoopConfig**: Configuration for orchestration (ProjectDir, MaxConcurrent, StaggerDelay, DedupTimeout)\n- **ListTasksFunc**: `func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) ([]Task, error)` - discovers available tasks\n- **MainFunc**: `func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, taskID string) (*RunResult, error)` - executes main workflow for a task\n- **FinalizeFunc**: `func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, taskID string, mainResult *RunResult) (*RunResult, error)` - optional cleanup after main completes\n- **Loop struct**: Manages continuous orchestration with support for both legacy (single-function) and three-phase modes\n\n**Three-Phase Loop Implementation (`runPhased()` method - lines 155-241):**\n1. Maintains concurrent limit with slot-filling logic\n2. Calls `pickTaskFromPhase()` to discover available work (line 187)\n3. Launches goroutines for each task that execute both main and finalize (lines 192-215):\n   - Phase 2 (Main): Executes the main workflow with context.Background() (line 198)\n   - Phase 3 (Finalize): Runs finalize if configured, on both success and failure (lines 207-212)\n4. Implements deduplication to prevent reassignment of the same task within DedupTimeout window (lines 256-265)\n5. Backsoff on failure with idlePollInterval (30 seconds) and immediately retries on success\n\n**Task Filtering:**\n- `pickTaskFromPhase()` (lines 246-283) uses `task.IsOpen()` to filter only open tasks\n- Tasks in non-open status (closed, in-progress) are skipped\n\n**Legacy Support:**\n- `NewLoop()` for single-function mode (existing behavior)\n- `NewPhaseLoop()` for three-phase mode (new)\n- `runLegacy()` maintains backward compatibility\n\n---\n\n#### **2. `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`** (Task Structures)\n\n**Task Structure** (lines 22-28):\n```go\ntype Task struct {\n    ID          string            `json:\"id\"`\n    Status      string            `json:\"status\"`\n    Title       string            `json:\"title\"`\n    Description string            `json:\"description\"`\n    Metadata    map[string]string `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**TaskStatus Constants** (lines 15-19):\n- `TaskStatusOpen = \"open\"`\n- `TaskStatusClosed = \"closed\"`\n- `TaskStatusInProgress = \"in-progress\"`\n\n**IsOpen() Method** (lines 31-33): Returns true if status is \"open\" or empty (backward compatible)\n\n**Task Parsing:**\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner`: Runs shell command, parses JSON array output (lines 42-67)\n- `ParseTasksJSONL()` (lines 72-89): Parses JSONL format (one JSON object per line) for list-tasks output\n  - Each line represents one task\n  - Empty lines are skipped\n  - Returns error on invalid JSON\n\n**ReadListTasksOutput()** in loop.go (lines 440-473): Utility to read output directory from list-tasks run and parse JSONL\n\n---\n\n#### **3. `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`** (Step Execution)\n\n**Executor Structure** (lines 51-63):\n- `TaskID`: Optional task ID assigned by daemon loop (line 61)\n- `ExtraEnv`: Additional environment variables passed to all steps (line 62)\n- `HostRunID`: ID of parent host run (line 58)\n\n**Environment Variables Passed to Steps** (lines 95-122):\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`: Project directory (line 96)\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`: Output file path for the step (line 97)\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`: Daemon-assigned task ID (line 102)\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`: Previous step's output (line 112)\n- Additional output mappings from wires (lines 116-122)\n- ExtraEnv variables (e.g., finalize phase outcome vars) (lines 105-108)\n\n**Step Types Executed** (lines 78-87):\n- Script steps (run shell commands)\n- Workflow steps (dispatch container workflows)\n- Agent steps (run coding agents on host)\n\n---\n\n#### **4. `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`** (Workflow Execution)\n\n**RunResult Structure** (lines 29-34):\n```go\ntype RunResult struct {\n    RunID     string\n    State     domain.RunState\n    OutputDir string\n}\n```\n\n**Named Workflow Execution:**\n- `RunNamed()` (lines 50-53): Executes a named workflow from host.cloche\n- `runNamedWorkflow()` (lines 57-149): Core implementation\n  - Parses `dsl.ParseAllForHost()` to get multiple workflows from host.cloche (line 64)\n  - Looks up specific workflow by name (lines 69-72)\n  - Creates output directory at `.cloche/<orchRunID>/output` (lines 75-78)\n  - Persists host run as IsHost=true in store (lines 83-90)\n  - Creates Executor with TaskID and ExtraEnv propagation (lines 92-102)\n\n**Workflow-Level Agent Configuration** (lines 105-110):\n- `host.agent_command` and `host.agent_args` keys\n- Parsed and passed to executor for agent steps\n\n---\n\n#### **5. `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`** (Multiple Workflows)\n\n**ParseAllForHost()** (lines 45-67):\n- Parses host.cloche files containing multiple workflows\n- Returns `map[string]*domain.Workflow`\n- Validates no duplicate workflow names (lines 56-58)\n- Requires at least one workflow (lines 62-64)\n\n**Location Validation** (line 156):\n- Sets `domain.LocationHost` for host workflows\n- Enables location-based validation\n\n---\n\n#### **6. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** (Daemon Integration)\n\n**ClocheServer Fields** (lines 28-41):\n- `loops`: `map[string]*host.Loop` - orchestration loop per project (line 40)\n- `runIDs`: Track run_id -> container_id mapping\n\n**Server Initialization:**\n- `NewClocheServer()` initializes loops map (line 48)\n- `NewClocheServerWithCaptures()` adds capture and log store support (line 59)\n\n**Orchestration Loop Not Directly Shown** in excerpts, but the server manages lifecycle and dispatches workflows that feed into the loop\n\n---\n\n### **Documentation Files**\n\n#### **1. `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`** (Complete)\n\n**Workflow Locations**:\n- **Container workflows**: Run in Docker containers via cloche-agent (script or agent steps only)\n- **Host workflows**: Run on host machine as daemon process (script, agent, or workflow steps)\n\n**Step Types**:\n- **agent** (has `prompt`): Invokes coding agent\n- **script** (has `run`): Runs shell command\n- **workflow** (has `workflow_name`): Dispatches container workflow (host only)\n\n**Host Workflow Example** (lines 160-192):\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n    CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output[0].id,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY = output[0].description\n  ]\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n**Wire Output Mappings** (lines 101-133):\n- Extract values from step output and inject as environment variables\n- Support JSON path expressions: `output`, `output.key`, `output[N]`, `output.a.b.c`, etc.\n\n**Host Configuration Block** (lines 136-154):\n- `host {}` block for workflow-level agent defaults\n- Supports `agent_command` and `agent_args`\n- Step-level overrides take priority\n\n**Execution Model** (lines 199-212):\n- Container workflows: Agent walks graph inside container\n- Host workflows: Daemon walks graph on host; scripts run from main git worktree\n- Environment variables injected: `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, etc.\n\n---\n\n#### **2. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`** (System Architecture)\n\n**System Components**:\n- **cloche** (CLI): Short-lived client\n- **cloched** (Daemon): Long-running orchestrator\n- **cloche-agent** (In-Container): Autonomous agent\n\n**Execution Model**:\n- One container per workflow run\n- All steps execute in same container\n- Container lifecycle: pull/build image → copy project → start container → stream status → extract results → stop\n\n**Communication**:\n- Agent <-> Daemon: JSON-lines over stdout\n- CLI <-> Daemon: gRPC\n\n**Capture System**: Record step inputs/outputs/results for replay\n\n---\n\n#### **3. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`** (Host Workflow Design)\n\n**Problem Solved**: Extension point for custom orchestration strategies\n\n**Solution**: `host.cloche` file with special workflow location for host execution\n\n**New Step Type: `workflow`**:\n- `workflow_name` config key dispatches container workflow\n- `prompt_step` optional override for which step's output to read\n- Results: `success` (RunStateSucceeded), `fail` (RunStateFailed/RunStateCancelled)\n\n**Step Output Capture**:\n- Every host step writes output to: `.cloche/<orch-run-id>/output/<step_name>.out`\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` passed to next step\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` tells step where to write its output\n\n**Environment Variables Injected** (lines 92-105):\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`: Task being processed\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE`: Task summary\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_BODY`: Full task description\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`: Project directory path\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`: Where step writes output\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`: Previous step's output file\n\n**Default `host.cloche`** (lines 180-199):\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  prepare-prompt:fail -> abort\n  develop:success -> done\n  develop:fail -> done\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Test Coverage**\n\n#### **`/workspace/internal/host/loop_test.go`**\n\n**Legacy Mode Tests**:\n- `TestLoop_StartStop`: Basic start/stop\n- `TestLoop_RampsUpOnSuccess`: Immediate retry on success, backoff on failure\n- `TestLoop_TaskAssigner_PassesTaskID`: Task ID propagation\n- `TestLoop_TaskAssigner_DedupPreventsReassignment`: Deduplication window\n- `TestLoop_TaskAssigner_DedupExpires`: Dedup timeout expiration\n\n**Three-Phase Mode Tests** (NewPhaseLoop):\n- `TestPhaseLoop_BasicFlow`: list-tasks → main → finalize flow\n- `TestPhaseLoop_SkipsClosedTasks`: Only picks open tasks\n- `TestPhaseLoop_FinalizeRunsOnFailure`: Finalize receives failed state\n- `TestPhaseLoop_NoFinalize`: Optional finalize (nil is valid)\n- `TestPhaseLoop_DedupFiltersOpenTasks`: Dedup works across phases\n\n#### **`/workspace/internal/host/task_test.go`**\n\n**ScriptTaskAssigner Tests**:\n- JSON array parsing\n- Empty array handling\n- Command failures\n- Invalid JSON handling\n- Partial fields\n\n**JSONL Parsing Tests**:\n- Basic JSONL with multiple tasks\n- Metadata fields\n- Empty lines\n- Invalid JSON in middle of JSONL\n- Task status variations\n\n**Task.IsOpen() Tests**:\n- Status field values: \"open\" (true), \"\" (true for backward compat), \"closed\" (false), \"in-progress\" (false)\n\n#### **`/workspace/internal/host/executor_test.go`**\n\n**Output Mapping Tests**: Large test file testing:\n- Output mapping from wires\n- Step output file capture\n- Environment variable injection\n- Executor setup with tasks, projects, etc.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Architectural Patterns**\n\n1. **Three-Phase Separation of Concerns**:\n   - List-Tasks: Pure discovery (reads external state)\n   - Main: Work execution (full computation)\n   - Finalize: Cleanup/side effects (post-execution)\n\n2. **Deduplication Strategy**: \n   - Prevents rapid reassignment of same task\n   - Timeout-based window (default 5 minutes)\n   - Stored per-loop instance in memory\n\n3. **Concurrent Slot Management**:\n   - Up to MaxConcurrent (default 1) active runs\n   - Stagger delay between launches to avoid race conditions\n   - Immediate retry on success, idle backoff on failure\n\n4. **Environment Variable Propagation**:\n   - Task metadata (ID, title, body) injected into steps\n   - Previous output passed as `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`\n   - Wire output mappings extract/transform values\n   - ExtraEnv for finalize phase outcome variables\n\n5. **Output File Organization**:\n   - Per-step: `.cloche/<orch-run-id>/output/<step_name>.out`\n   - Findable by ReadListTasksOutput() for JSONL parsing\n\n6. **Backward Compatibility**:\n   - NewLoop() for legacy single-function mode\n   - NewPhaseLoop() for three-phase\n   - Both coexist; selection based on which functions are set\n\n---\n\n### **File Paths (Absolute)**\n\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`\n- `/workspace/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/workspace/README.md`"}],"totalDurationMs":59181,"totalTokens":68846,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1926,"cache_read_input_tokens":62898,"output_tokens":4020,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1926},"inference_geo":"","i